# Agent Communication Protocol

Agents must communicate using shared files, not hidden assumptions.

## Required Shared Files

For every medium or large task, create or update:

- .cursor/team/tasks/TASK-[id].md
- .cursor/team/handoffs/HANDOFF-[id]-[agent].md
- .cursor/team/reviews/REVIEW-[id].md when reviewed
- .cursor/team/decisions/ADR-[id].md for important decisions

## Handoff Format

Every handoff must include:

- Agent name
- Task ID
- Summary
- Files inspected
- Files changed
- Integration points
- Risks
- Tests/checks run
- Next agent recommendation

## Logic and Algorithm Communication

For any task involving calculation, data processing, search, matching, ranking, filtering, aggregation, report generation, finance, measurement, quantity, pricing, or optimization:

- Logic & Algorithm Engineer must create a logic analysis before implementation.
- Engineering agents must follow the approved logic analysis.
- QA must use the test cases from Logic & Algorithm Engineer.
- If implementation changes the approved logic, Code Reviewer must check and document the reason.

## Conflict Rules

- Do not overwrite another agent's handoff.
- Do not mark task complete if another required agent has unresolved blockers.
- Architecture conflict: Solution Architect decides.
- Security risk: Security Engineer can block.
- Test failure: QA Engineer can block.
- Duplicate implementation: Code Reviewer can block.
- Logic/calculation error: Logic & Algorithm Engineer can block.
- Final coordination: Orchestrator decides.
